track_notes: There is a posted sign on pole at parking spot.  This is due to a nearby property corner.  If you follow the track file you will almost immediatly be on National Forest property.

0.93 miles with 600 EG hike primarily along an old logging road.  We entered the woods at 36.01966, -81.71204 but turned almost immediately to the left (N) and climbed steeply to the ridge line where you will pick up the logging road that you will basically follow the rest of the way.  This short and steep <100 foot section is the only bushwhacking along the way.  About a third of a mile in, the logging road will turn to the right.  You can climb the Ridgeline off trail for a short distance to rejoin the road or take the slightly longer road route.  Where the road meets the ridge line again at 0.57 miles is the start of the long AZ.  On the way back down when you reach a flat area (36.02094, -81.70969), veer to the right to retrace your route back down.
